{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-15",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_15_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Every Crackpot",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 499.82,
  "page_end_sec": 742.12,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.639,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 499.82,
      "end": 500.82,
      "text": "You and the police haven't"
    },
    {
      "start": 500.82,
      "end": 501.94,
      "text": "been hitting it off so well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 502.06,
      "end": 502.48,
      "text": "have you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 503.488,
      "end": 506.4,
      "text": "Spade made a negligent gesture with the fingers of his right",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 506.4,
      "end": 506.72,
      "text": "hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 507.712,
      "end": 508.14,
      "text": "Nothing serious,"
    },
    {
      "start": 508.68,
      "end": 509.5,
      "text": "he said lightly."
    },
    {
      "start": 510.464,
      "end": 511.64,
      "text": "Dundy gets too enthusiastic."
    },
    {
      "start": 513.1,
      "end": 514.14,
      "text": "The door opened to admit",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 514.22,
      "end": 514.76,
      "text": "two men."
    },
    {
      "start": 515.56,
      "end": 516.96,
      "text": "The one to whom Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.12,
      "end": 517.48,
      "text": "hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.58,
      "end": 517.94,
      "text": "Thomas,"
    },
    {
      "start": 518.72,
      "end": 521.24,
      "text": "was a sunburned stocky man of thirty in clothing and"
    },
    {
      "start": 521.4,
      "end": 523.08,
      "text": "hair of a kindred unruliness."
    },
    {
      "start": 523.58,
      "end": 526.36,
      "text": "He clapped Spade on his shoulder with a freckled hand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 526.6,
      "end": 527.0,
      "text": "asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 527.424,
      "end": 527.82,
      "text": "How's tricks?"
    },
    {
      "start": 528.16,
      "end": 529.54,
      "text": "and sat down beside him."
    },
    {
      "start": 530.0,
      "end": 532.28,
      "text": "The second man was younger and colorless."
    },
    {
      "start": 532.58,
      "end": 533.84,
      "text": "He took a seat a"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.84,
      "end": 535.56,
      "text": "little apart from the others and balanced"
    },
    {
      "start": 535.56,
      "end": 537.58,
      "text": "a stenographer's notebook on his knee,"
    },
    {
      "start": 537.74,
      "end": 538.44,
      "text": "holding a"
    },
    {
      "start": 538.5,
      "end": 539.7,
      "text": "green pencil over it."
    },
    {
      "start": 540.64,
      "end": 541.84,
      "text": "Spade glanced his way,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 542.0,
      "end": 542.68,
      "text": "chuckled,"
    },
    {
      "start": 542.68,
      "end": 543.4,
      "text": "and asked Bryan:"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.66,
      "end": 545.38,
      "text": "Anything I say will"
    },
    {
      "start": 545.52,
      "end": 546.44,
      "text": "be used against me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 546.58,
      "end": 548.82,
      "text": "The District Attorney smiled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 549.84,
      "end": 550.84,
      "text": "That always holds good."
    },
    {
      "start": 551.1,
      "end": 552.68,
      "text": "He took his glasses off,"
    },
    {
      "start": 552.76,
      "end": 553.4,
      "text": "looked at them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 553.42,
      "end": 554.92,
      "text": "and set them on his nose again."
    },
    {
      "start": 555.96,
      "end": 557.76,
      "text": "He looked through them at Spade and asked:"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.22,
      "end": 559.32,
      "text": "Who killed Thursby?"
    },
    {
      "start": 559.65,
      "end": 560.76,
      "text": "Spade said:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 560.94,
      "end": 561.92,
      "text": "I don't know."
    },
    {
      "start": 563.008,
      "end": 565.24,
      "text": "Bryan rubbed his black eyeglass-ribbon between",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 565.34,
      "end": 567.14,
      "text": "thumb and fingers and said knowingly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 567.2,
      "end": 568.82,
      "text": "Perhaps you don't,"
    },
    {
      "start": 569.14,
      "end": 570.4,
      "text": "but you certainly could make an"
    },
    {
      "start": 570.56,
      "end": 571.26,
      "text": "excellent guess."
    },
    {
      "start": 571.54,
      "end": 571.64,
      "text": "Maybe,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 572.8,
      "end": 573.84,
      "text": "but I wouldn't."
    },
    {
      "start": 574.82,
      "end": 576.58,
      "text": "The District Attorney raised his eyebrows.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 577.44,
      "end": 578.38,
      "text": "I wouldn't,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 578.38,
      "end": 579.22,
      "text": "Spade repeated."
    },
    {
      "start": 580.0,
      "end": 580.8,
      "text": "He was serene."
    },
    {
      "start": 582.0,
      "end": 584.52,
      "text": "My guess might be excellent, or it might be crummy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 584.64,
      "end": 585.42,
      "text": "but Mrs."
    },
    {
      "start": 585.52,
      "end": 588.1,
      "text": "Spade didn't raise any children dippy enough"
    },
    {
      "start": 588.66,
      "end": 590.36,
      "text": "to make guesses in front of a district"
    },
    {
      "start": 590.48,
      "end": 590.82,
      "text": "attorney,"
    },
    {
      "start": 591.04,
      "end": 592.88,
      "text": "an assistant district attorney,"
    },
    {
      "start": 593.04,
      "end": 594.12,
      "text": "and a stenographer."
    },
    {
      "start": 595.56,
      "end": 597.04,
      "text": "Why shouldn't you, if you've nothing",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 597.26,
      "end": 597.62,
      "text": "to conceal."
    },
    {
      "start": 598.08,
      "end": 598.18,
      "text": "Everybody,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 599.88,
      "end": 601.46,
      "text": "Spade responded mildly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 601.52,
      "end": 603.1,
      "text": "has something to conceal."
    },
    {
      "start": 604.36,
      "end": 605.0,
      "text": "And you have—?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 606.14,
      "end": 606.66,
      "text": "My guesses,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 606.86,
      "end": 607.7,
      "text": "for one thing."
    },
    {
      "start": 608.96,
      "end": 612.18,
      "text": "The District Attorney looked down at his desk and then up at Spade.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 612.84,
      "end": 613.42,
      "text": "He settled his"
    },
    {
      "start": 613.52,
      "end": 615.12,
      "text": "glasses more firmly on his nose."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.88,
      "end": 616.24,
      "text": "He said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 616.82,
      "end": 619.1,
      "text": "If you'd prefer not having the stenographer here,"
    },
    {
      "start": 619.48,
      "end": 620.52,
      "text": "we can dismiss him."
    },
    {
      "start": 621.6,
      "end": 623.34,
      "text": "It was simply as a matter of convenience"
    },
    {
      "start": 624.1,
      "end": 625.02,
      "text": "that I brought him in."
    },
    {
      "start": 626.16,
      "end": 626.6,
      "text": "I don't mind",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 626.82,
      "end": 627.58,
      "text": "him a damned bit,"
    },
    {
      "start": 627.78,
      "end": 628.34,
      "text": "Spade replied."
    },
    {
      "start": 628.76,
      "end": 631.44,
      "text": "I'm willing to have anything I say put down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 631.78,
      "end": 632.78,
      "text": "and I'm willing to sign"
    },
    {
      "start": 632.78,
      "end": 632.98,
      "text": "it."
    },
    {
      "start": 633.8,
      "end": 636.1,
      "text": "We don't intend asking you to sign anything,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 636.46,
      "end": 637.44,
      "text": "Bryan assured him."
    },
    {
      "start": 637.58,
      "end": 639.42,
      "text": "I wish you wouldn't regard this"
    },
    {
      "start": 639.42,
      "end": 641.32,
      "text": "as a formal inquiry at all,"
    },
    {
      "start": 641.92,
      "end": 643.88,
      "text": "and please don't think I've any belief,"
    },
    {
      "start": 644.06,
      "end": 645.48,
      "text": "much less confidence,"
    },
    {
      "start": 646.04,
      "end": 648.32,
      "text": "in those theories the police seem to have formed."
    },
    {
      "start": 648.56,
      "end": 648.66,
      "text": "No?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 649.62,
      "end": 651.2,
      "text": "Not a particle.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 651.54,
      "end": 653.42,
      "text": "Spade sighed and crossed his",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 653.58,
      "end": 653.8,
      "text": "legs."
    },
    {
      "start": 654.17,
      "end": 655.34,
      "text": "I'm glad of that."
    },
    {
      "start": 656.22,
      "end": 658.38,
      "text": "He felt in his pockets for tobacco and papers."
    },
    {
      "start": 659.328,
      "end": 659.87,
      "text": "What's your theory?"
    },
    {
      "start": 660.96,
      "end": 663.22,
      "text": "Bryan leaned forward in his chair and his eyes",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 663.22,
      "end": 665.62,
      "text": "were hard and shiny as the lenses over them."
    },
    {
      "start": 666.46,
      "end": 668.3,
      "text": "Tell me who Archer was shadowing Thursby"
    },
    {
      "start": 668.3,
      "end": 670.52,
      "text": "for and I'll tell you who killed Thursby."
    },
    {
      "start": 671.552,
      "end": 673.56,
      "text": "Spade's laugh was brief and scornful.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 674.56,
      "end": 675.62,
      "text": "You're as wrong as Dundy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 675.7,
      "end": 676.12,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 677.408,
      "end": 678.46,
      "text": "Don't misunderstand me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 678.5,
      "end": 678.88,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 679.02,
      "end": 679.72,
      "text": "Bryan said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 679.94,
      "end": 681.7,
      "text": "knocking on the desk with his knuckles."
    },
    {
      "start": 682.08,
      "end": 684.28,
      "text": "I don't say your client killed Thursby,"
    },
    {
      "start": 684.4,
      "end": 685.34,
      "text": "or had him killed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 685.96,
      "end": 687.04,
      "text": "but I do say that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.488,
      "end": 689.68,
      "text": "knowing who your client is, or was,"
    },
    {
      "start": 689.92,
      "end": 692.24,
      "text": "I'll mighty soon know who killed Thursby."
    },
    {
      "start": 693.248,
      "end": 694.4,
      "text": "Spade lighted his cigarette,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 694.68,
      "end": 696.14,
      "text": "removed it from his lips,"
    },
    {
      "start": 696.28,
      "end": 697.9,
      "text": "emptied his lungs of smoke,"
    },
    {
      "start": 697.96,
      "end": 699.36,
      "text": "and spoke as if puzzled:"
    },
    {
      "start": 699.59,
      "end": 701.56,
      "text": "I don't exactly get that."
    },
    {
      "start": 702.62,
      "end": 703.28,
      "text": "You don't?"
    },
    {
      "start": 703.32,
      "end": 705.2,
      "text": "Then suppose I put it this way."
    },
    {
      "start": 705.46,
      "end": 707.78,
      "text": "Where is Dixie Monahan?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 708.8,
      "end": 710.66,
      "text": "Spade's face retained its puzzled look.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 711.38,
      "end": 713.04,
      "text": "Putting it that way doesn't help much,"
    },
    {
      "start": 713.16,
      "end": 713.5,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 713.84,
      "end": 714.86,
      "text": "I still don't get it."
    },
    {
      "start": 715.92,
      "end": 717.44,
      "text": "The District Attorney took his glasses",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 717.44,
      "end": 718.9,
      "text": "off and shook them for emphasis."
    },
    {
      "start": 719.94,
      "end": 720.3,
      "text": "He said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 721.0,
      "end": 723.48,
      "text": "We know Thursby was Monahan's bodyguard"
    },
    {
      "start": 723.66,
      "end": 727.9,
      "text": "and went with him when Monahan found it wise to vanish from Chicago."
    },
    {
      "start": 728.92,
      "end": 731.28,
      "text": "We know Monahan welshed on something like"
    },
    {
      "start": 731.28,
      "end": 734.24,
      "text": "two-hundred-thousand-dollars' worth of bets when he vanished."
    },
    {
      "start": 734.54,
      "end": 736.04,
      "text": "We don't know—"
    },
    {
      "start": 736.12,
      "end": 736.86,
      "text": "not yet—"
    },
    {
      "start": 737.04,
      "end": 738.7,
      "text": "who his creditors were."
    },
    {
      "start": 739.28,
      "end": 742.12,
      "text": "He put the glasses on again and smiled grimly."
    }
  ],
  "corrected": "claude"
}